    PDF Export


        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        #contentToPrint {
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }
        #exportBtn {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 16px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        #exportBtn:hover {
            background-color: #45a049;
        }
        iframe {
            width: 100%;
            height: 600px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }



    Export to PDF



&lt;script&gt;
    document.getElementById(&#039;exportBtn&#039;).addEventListener(&#039;click&#039;, function() {
        // Get the element to print
        const element = document.getElementById(&#039;contentToPrint&#039;);

        // Options for PDF generation
        const opt = {
            margin: 10,
            filename: &#039;exported_page.pdf&#039;,
            image: { type: &#039;jpeg&#039;, quality: 0.98 },
            html2canvas: { 
                scale: 2,
                useCORS: true,
                allowTaint: true,
                logging: true,
                scrollX: 0,
                scrollY: 0
            },
            jsPDF: { unit: &#039;mm&#039;, format: &#039;a4&#039;, orientation: &#039;portrait&#039; }
        };

        // Generate PDF
        html2pdf().from(element).set(opt).save();
    });
&lt;/script&gt;

网页PDF导出保留元素.content:
🤖 Assistant
I’ll create an HTML file with PDF export functionality that preserves the webpage elements. This will use html2pdf.js library for converting the content to PDF. Here’s the complete solution:
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;
    &lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&quot;&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;PDF Export&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;script src=&quot;cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/html2pdf.js/0.10.1/html2pdf.bundle.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        #contentToPrint {
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }
        #exportBtn {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 16px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        #exportBtn:hover {
            background-color: #45a049;
        }
        iframe {
            width: 100%;
            height: 600px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;button id=&quot;exportBtn&quot;&gt;Export to PDF&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;div id=&quot;contentToPrint&quot;&gt;
        &lt;iframe src=&quot;metaso.cn/search/8623131157501214720/interactive
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;script&gt;
        document.getElementById(&#039;exportBtn&#039;).addEventListener(&#039;click&#039;, function() {
            // Get the element to print
            const element = document.getElementById(&#039;contentToPrint&#039;);

            // Options for PDF generation
            const opt = {
                margin: 10,
                filename: &#039;exported_page.pdf&#039;,
                image: { type: &#039;jpeg&#039;, quality: 0.98 },
                html2canvas: { 
                    scale: 2,
                    useCORS: true,
                    allowTaint: true,
                    logging: true,
                    scrollX: 0,
                    scrollY: 0
                },
                jsPDF: { unit: &#039;mm&#039;, format: &#039;a4&#039;, orientation: &#039;portrait&#039; }
            };

            // Generate PDF
            html2pdf().from(element).set(opt).save();
        });
    &lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
This solution includes:

A button to trigger the PDF export
An iframe that displays the target webpage (metaso.cn/search/8623131157501214720/interactive)
PDF generation using html2pdf.js library with configuration options for:


Margins
File name
Image quality
Scaling
PDF format (A4)
CORS handling for iframe content

Note: Due to browser security restrictions, the PDF export of iframe content may be limited if the target website doesn’t explicitly allow framing. If you encounter issues, you might need to:

Use a server-side solution
Get permission from the target website to frame their content
Use a screenshot API as an alternative approach

The html2pdf.js library handles most modern browser requirements and provides good quality PDF output while preserving the visual appearance of the content.
